{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011AVgZ4SnXquiHct6QCcfEc","type":"tool_result","content":"variable\tvalue\tsetting_type\tpublic\tdescription\tdefault_value\torigin\nadmission.disk_bandwidth_tokens.elastic.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\twhen true, and provisioned bandwidth for the disk corresponding to a store is configured, tokens for elastic work will be limited if disk bandwidth becomes a bottleneck\ttrue\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.adjustment_delta_per_second\t0.001\tf\tf\tsets the per-second % adjustment used when when adapting elastic work CPU %s\t0.001\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.enabled\ttrue\tb\tf\twhen true, elastic work (like backups) performed by the KV layer is subject to admission control\ttrue\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.inactive_point\t0.1\tf\tf\tthe point between {min,max}_utilization the CPU % decreases to when there's no elastic work\t0.1\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.max_utilization\t0.75\tf\tf\tsets the ceiling on per-node elastic work CPU % utilization\t0.75\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.min_utilization\t0.05\tf\tf\tsets the floor on per-node elastic work CPU % utilization\t0.05\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.multiplicative_factor_on_decrease\t2\tf\tf\tsets the multiplier on negative adjustments to elastic work CPU %\t2\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.multiplicative_factor_on_inactive_decrease\t0.25\tf\tf\tsets the multiplier on negative adjustments to elastic work CPU % when inactive\t0.25\tdefault\nadmission.elastic_cpu.scheduler_latency_target\t1ms\td\tf\tsets the p99 scheduling latency the elastic CPU controller aims for\t1ms\tdefault\nadmission.epoch_lifo.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\twhen true, epoch-LIFO behavior is enabled when there is significant delay in admission\tfalse\tdefault\nadmission.epoch_lifo.epoch_closing_delta_duration\t5ms\td\tt\tthe delta duration before closing an epoch, for epoch-LIFO admission control ordering\t5ms\tdefault\nadmission.epoch_lifo.epoch_duration\t100ms\td\tt\tthe duration of an epoch, for epoch-LIFO admission control ordering\t100ms\tdefault\nadmission.epoch_lifo.queue_delay_threshold_to_switch_to_lifo\t105ms\td\tt\tthe queue delay encountered by a (tenant,priority) for switching to epoch-LIFO ordering\t105ms\tdefault\nadmission.kv.bulk_only.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\twhen both admission.kv.enabled and this is true, only throttle bulk work\tfalse\tdefault\nadmission.kv.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\twhen true, work performed by the KV layer is subject to admission control\ttrue\tdefault\nadmission.kv.pause_replication_io_threshold\t0\tf\tf\tpause replication to non-essential followers when their I/O admission control score exceeds the given threshold (zero to disable)\t0\tdefault\nadmission.kv.stores.tenant_weights.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\twhen true, tenant weights are enabled for KV-stores admission control\tfalse\tdefault\nadmission.kv.tenant_weights.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\twhen true, tenant weights are enabled for KV admission control\tfalse\tdefault\nadmission.kv_slot_adjuster.overload_threshold\t32\ti\tf\twhen the number of runnable goroutines per CPU is greater than this threshold, the slot adjuster considers the cpu to be overloaded\t32\tdefault\nadmission.l0_file_count_overload_threshold\t1000\ti\tf\twhen the L0 file count exceeds this theshold, the store is considered overloaded\t1000\tdefault\nadmission.l0_min_size_per_sub_level\t5242880\ti\tf\twhen non-zero, this indicates the minimum size that is needed to count towards one sub-level\t5242880\tdefault\nadmission.l0_sub_level_count_overload_threshold\t20\ti\tf\twhen the L0 sub-level count exceeds this threshold, the store is considered overloaded\t20\tdefault\nadmission.min_flush_util_fraction\t0.5\tf\tf\twhen computing flush tokens, this fraction is a lower bound on the dynamically adjusted flush utilization target fraction that attempts to reduce write stalls. Set it to a high fraction (>>1, e.g. 10), to disable flush based tokens. The dynamic target fraction is used to multiply the