{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017D1bL5M73HnHM3AEH8731m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VUDKakGpbeERYSjGtgD1Hm","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n cockroachdb create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'AUDIT_EOF'\nCockroachDB Compliance Configuration Audit\n===========================================\nAudit Date : 2026-06-25\nAuditor    : Automated READ-ONLY inspection (no cluster changes made)\nCluster ID : faf2e95e-4656-428a-b7cf-ae7fd18e1918\nVersion    : CockroachDB CCL v24.1.0 (built 2024-05-15)\n\n--- NODE COUNT & HEALTH ---\nTotal nodes   : 3\nAll available : YES\nAll live      : YES\n\nNode details:\n  Node 1  crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257  available=true  live=true\n  Node 2  crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257  available=true  live=true\n  Node 3  crdb-cluster-2.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257  available=true  live=true\n\nStatefulSet: crdb-cluster  READY=3/3\n\n--- NON-DEFAULT CLUSTER SETTINGS ---\n(Only settings whose current value differs from the CockroachDB factory default are listed.)\n\n  diagnostics.reporting.enabled  =  true          (default: false)\n    * Telemetry reporting is ENABLED.\n\n  kv.range_merge.queue.enabled   =  false         (default: true)\n    * Automatic range merging is DISABLED. Ranges will not be merged\n      back together when they shrink below the minimum size threshold.\n\n  kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate =  208 MiB       (default: 32 MiB)\n    * Rebalance snapshot bandwidth cap raised ~6.5x above default.\n      Allows faster rebalancing but increases network/IO pressure\n      during rebalance events.\n\n  version                        =  24.1           (not a user-set tunable; reflects cluster version)\n  cluster.secret                 =  (UUID, redacted for audit)\n\n--- ZONE CONFIGURATIONS ---\n(Zones shown are those explicitly configured; factory defaults not listed separately.)\n\n  RANGE default\n    num_replicas  : 3\n    gc.ttlseconds : 14400  (4 h)\n    range_min_bytes / range_max_bytes : 128 MiB / 512 MiB\n\n  RANGE liveness   (node liveness heartbeats)\n    num_replicas  : 5\n    gc.ttlseconds : 600    (10 min)\n\n  RANGE meta       (range addressing metadata)\n    num_replicas  : 5\n    gc.ttlseconds : 3600   (1 h)\n\n  RANGE system\n    num_replicas  : 5\n    gc.ttlseconds : 14400  (4 h)\n\n  DATABASE system\n    num_replicas  : 5\n    gc.ttlseconds : 14400  (4 h)\n\n  TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c  (custom zone)\n    num_replicas  : 3\n    gc.ttlseconds : 14400  (4 h)\n\n  TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d  (custom zone)\n    num_replicas  : 3\n    gc.ttlseconds : 14400  (4 h)\n\n  System table overrides (GC TTL only):\n    system.public.lease                         gc.ttlseconds = 600   (10 min)\n    system.public.replication_constraint_stats  gc.ttlseconds = 600   (10 min)\n    system.public.replication_stats             gc.ttlseconds = 600   (10 min)\n    system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries  gc.ttlseconds = 3600  (1 h)\n    system.public.statement_activity            gc.ttlseconds = 3600  (1 h)\n    system.public.statement_statistics          gc.ttlseconds = 3600  (1 h)\n    system.public.tenant_usage                  gc.ttlseconds = 7200  (2 h)\n    system.public.transaction_activity          gc.ttlseconds = 3600  (1 h)\n    system.public.transaction_statistics        gc.ttlseconds = 3600  (1 h)\n\n--- REPLICATION SUMMARY ---\nDefault replication factor : 3  (RANGE default)\nSystem/meta/liveness zones : 5  (higher durability for critical ranges)\nTenant table zones         : 3  (tenant_b.table_c, tenant_b.table_d)\n  Note: tenant_a tables (table_a, table_b) inherit the RANGE default (3 replicas).\n\n--- DATABASES & SCHEMAS ---\nDatabases : defaultdb, postgres, system\nSchemas in defaultdb:\n  tenant_a  ->  table_a (1 estimated row), table_b (0 rows)\n  tenant_b  ->  table_c (1 estimated row), table_d (1 estimated row)\n\n--- NOTABLE FINDINGS FOR COMPLIANCE REVIEW ---\n1. kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate is set to 208 MiB (6.5x the 32 MiB default).\n   This is a deliberate performance tuning choice; verify it is intentional and\n   documented in the change-management record.\n\n2. kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false disables automatic range consolidation.\n   This may be intentional to prevent range churn during a migration or to keep\n   pre-split ranges stable. Confirm this is expected for the maintenance window.\n\n3. diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true sends usage telemetry to Cockroach Labs.\n   Confirm this is permitted under the organization's data-sharing policy.\n\n4. System/critical ranges (liveness, meta, system) use num_replicas=5 even though\n   the cluster has only 3 nodes. With 3 nodes the effective replication is capped\n   at 3; the zone config aspirational value of 5 will not be satisfied until 2\n   additional nodes are added.\n\n5. Cluster is running in TLS/secure mode (SSL certs mounted at\n   /cockroach/cockroach-certs). No insecure access was used during this audit.\n\n--- END OF AUDIT ---\nAUDIT_EOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":644,"cache_read_input_tokens":37391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":644},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"275a3f81-6145-4c76-92bf-ff912a7fb5cd","uuid":"48c7122b-3089-4091-b904-aec433944783","request_id":"req_011CcQPY8QDbS9nDRq2xWTzF"}
